<DOC><DOCNO> AP881007-0212 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-10-07-88 0100EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r f PM-BusinessHighlights 2Takes   10-07 0462</FIRST><SECOND>PM-Business Highlights, 2 Takes,0484</SECOND><DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Texas Air Corp. appears to have put EasternAirlines on the auction block, just a few months after ChairmanFrank Lorenzo vowed to stockholders that the ailing subsidiary wasnot for sale.   Sources said Thursday that financier Carl Icahn, who heads TransWorld Airlines Inc., was talking with Lorenzo about acquiringMiami-based Eastern. A day earlier, New York developer Donald Trumpconfirmed he was bargaining with Texas Air about purchasingEastern's Northeast shuttle.   None of the parties would comment Thursday.</TEXT><DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   The Coniston Partners investment group hasproposed a friendly $1.13 billion takeover of foods giant TWServices Inc. but suggested it might turn hostile if the offer isrejected.   The proposal, which would pay $28 in cash for each of the 39.27million TW shares Coniston does not already own, was announcedThursday.   Coniston disclosed a 19 percent stake in Coniston last month, anindication it might move to buy the owner of the Denny's restaurantchain and other properties.</TEXT><DATELINE>BOSTON (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Digital Equipment Corp. says it has struck a dealto market personal computers manufactured by Tandy Corp., a movethat takes the heat off Digital to produce a personal computer ofits own.   Tandy will make personal computers to Digital's specifications,which Digital will market and sell under its brand, Digital saidThursday.</TEXT><DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   The Senate has seized one of the most popularissues of the presidential campaign and by 94-0 approved a taxexemption for interest on U.S. savings bonds that are used tofinance a college education.   The vote Thursday on an amendment to the tax-overhaul bill wassponsored by Sen. Edward M. Kennedy, D-Mass., who described it as``a simple, sensible way to help families save for college.''</TEXT><DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   The British government's demand that Kuwait halveits stake in British Petroleum Co. PLC has drawn fire from criticswho fear it may discourage foreign investment in the alreadydepressed London stock market.   The government said Thursday it acted to defend the free marketagainst a cartel, the Organization of Petroleum ExportingCountries, to which Kuwait belongs.   British Petroleum is Britain's largest company, and the PersianGulf nation of Kuwait is its biggest shareholder.</TEXT><DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   A federal appeals court has rejected an unusualrequest by Drexel Burnham Lambert Inc. to disqualify the judgepresiding over the government's fraud case against the Wall Streetfirm.   The U.S. 2nd Circuit Court of Appeals in Manhattan said Thursdayin a written ruling that the move by attorneys for Drexel and otherdefendants was premature because U.S. District Judge Milton Pollackhad not yet ruled on their motion to remove him from the case.</TEXT><NOTE>MORE</NOTE></DOC>